@@eSepulchur Pasture -- Compact Temples Advisory@@N

The @@WCompact Temples@@N maintain a standing advisory on Midgaard's
Sepulchur Pasture, shared at quarterly governance sessions. The
advisory is @@yclinical@@N -- because the Pasture demonstrates
institutional decay of the kind Kiess was designed to prevent.

Midgaard's burial field began as honest mercy. Road dead routed to
the @@dNinth Acre@@N, where shepherd-priests rang a bell at dusk. Names
copied from signet rings. Effects cataloged. Competent civic process.

Then volume overwhelmed capacity. The @@yTithe of Last Burdens@@N funded
guards, carts, salt, and bells. Those who could not pay were entered
as @@d"deferred names"@@N -- interred in common furrows pending claim.

@@rDeferred names.@@N The Compact Temples flag this phrase in red ink.
A deferred name is a @@rsealed obligation@@N: a promise to the dead
that no living office must fulfill on any schedule, binding
indefinitely, accumulating without audit. Precisely the kind of
instrument Kiess's founding charter was written to prohibit.

A quiet industry formed around grief: clerks charging for corrections,
carriers misplacing evidence, wardens delaying remains, brokers
trading inheritance rumor. The @@yTrade Syndics@@N recognize this as
@@rcorruption through deferral@@N -- when an obligation has no expiration,
intermediaries extract value from the gap between promise and
fulfillment.

The @@WViolet Compact's@@N containment doctrine expanded to the Pasture.
Certain remains forbidden immediate burial. Holding pens, wardwire
trenches, witness lanterns. The Compact called it public safety.
Temple mourners called it trapping souls in legal limbo. Neither
had authority to overrule the other -- the signature failure mode
of single-authority governance.

Then the @@rgravebell rang twice for every pull@@N: once from the tower,
once from beneath the furrows. Names recorded without bodies. Bodies
interred without names. "Deferred name" stopped meaning paperwork
and started meaning @@runrest@@N.

@@dWall Command@@N draws the operational conclusion: Midgaard's dead are
becoming an uncontrolled variable. If the Pasture destabilizes
districts that supply Roc Road patrols, Kiess convoys bear the cost.

@@yThe Prism teaches@@N: name the dead, pay the living, and let no
obligation outlive the office that issued it. Deferred names are
sealed warrants written against the voiceless. Kiess does not
defer. Kiess does not seal. When we bury our dead, we finish
the sentence.
